QE Technical Test Documentation.
This repository contains automated tests written in JavaScript using Selenium WebDriver to perform end-to-end testing on web applications. These tests aim to validate the functionality and behavior of web pages and ensure their proper functioning.

Getting Started
To run the tests in this repository, follow the steps below:

Prerequisites
Node.js and npm (Node Package Manager) must be installed on your system. You can download and install Node.js from the official website: https://nodejs.org.

Chrome Browser: The tests are designed to run on the Chrome browser. Make sure you have Google Chrome installed on your machine.

Installation
Clone this repository to your local machine using Git

git clone https://github.com/Ekow244/qe-test.github.io.git

Navigate to the project's root directory:

cd selenium-javascript-tests

Install the project dependencies using npm:

npm install

Running the Tests
To run the tests, execute the following command in the terminal:

node tests/*.js
or 
npm test to run all the tests

Test Results
After running the tests, you will see the test results in the terminal.